    <oops:Pitfall>
        <oops:Code>P04</oops:Code>
        <oops:Name>Creating unconnected ontology elements</oops:Name>
        <oops:Description>Ontology elements (classes, object properties and datatype properties) are created isolated, with no relation to the rest of the ontology.	</oops:Description>
        <oops:Importance>Minor</oops:Importance>
        <oops:NumberAffectedElements>1</oops:NumberAffectedElements>
        <oops:Affects>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Document</oops:AffectedElement>
        </oops:Affects>
    </oops:Pitfall>
    <oops:Pitfall>
        <oops:Code>P07</oops:Code>
        <oops:Name>Merging different concepts in the same class</oops:Name>
        <oops:Description>A class whose name refers to two or more different concepts is created.	</oops:Description>
        <oops:Importance>Minor</oops:Importance>
        <oops:NumberAffectedElements>8</oops:NumberAffectedElements>
        <oops:Affects>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#PlanningAndManagementActivity</oops:AffectedElement>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#BackupAndRecovery</oops:AffectedElement>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#VerificationAndValidationActivity</oops:AffectedElement>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#OperationsAndMaintenanceActivity</oops:AffectedElement>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#QualityAndGovernanceActivity</oops:AffectedElement>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#ReleaseAndDeploymentActivity</oops:AffectedElement>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#TrainingAndOnboarding</oops:AffectedElement>
            <oops:AffectedElement>http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#EvolutionAndImprovementActivity</oops:AffectedElement>
        </oops:Affects>
    </oops:Pitfall>
    <oops:Pitfall>
        <oops:Code>P08</oops:Code>
        <oops:Name>Missing annotations</oops:Name>
        <oops:Description>This pitfall consists in creating an ontology element and failing to provide human readable annotations attached to it. Consequently, ontology elements lack annotation properties that label them (e.g. rdfs:label, lemon:LexicalEntry, skos:prefLabel or skos:altLabel) or that define them (e.g. rdfs:comment or dc:description). This pitfall is related to the guidelines provided in [5].	</oops:Description>
        <oops:Importance>Minor</oops:Importance>
        <oops:NumberAffectedElements>208</oops:NumberAffectedElements>
